.TH echo 3
.SH NAME
\*Lecho\*O, \*Lnoecho\*O \- Enables or disables the terminal echo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O
.PP
\*Lint echo(\|)\*O

\*Lint noecho(\|)\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "echo subroutine"
.iX "noecho subroutine"
The \*Lecho\*O
routine enables echoing of characters typed by the user.
The \*Lnoecho\*O routine disables echoing of characters
typed by the user.
.PP
Initially, input characters are echoed.  Subsequent calls to
\*Lecho\*O and \*Lnoecho\*O do not flush typeahead.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lecho\*O and \*Lnoecho\*O functions return OK on
success and ERR on error.
.EQ
delim off
.EN
